plot:
El famoso presentador de Top Gear viaja alrededor del mundo en busca de diseños que hayan sido implementados y que, aun en la actualidad, consideraríamos de ciencia ficción. Serie producida por la BBC y la Open University.

James May's Big Ideas is a three-part British television miniseries in which James May, a journalist and self-acknowledged geek travels the globe in search of implementations for concepts widely considered science fiction, or his big ideas. The series is produced by the BBC and the Open University and began airing at 8pm on Sundays on 28 September 2008. (Wikipedia)
